Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Chapter 9  -  Section 9.8", "Title",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  "I",
  StyleBox["n this ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" notebook, you will analyze the equation leading to the \
eigenvalues for a perturbation of the Lorenz equations with parameter r. You \
will use ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" to factor the cubic and evaluate the solutions for different \
values of this parameter. The exact value of the parameter where a \
bifurcation exists will be determined.\n",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "\n",
  StyleBox["In most cases, to adapt this code to other problems, you will \
have to change only the input shown in red. To open a cell grouping, \
double-click on the right-hand side of the double cell marker.",
    FontSize->14]
}], "Subsubtitle",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
  "Problem 3:  \t3",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[Lambda]\^3\)]],
  "+ 41",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[Lambda]\^2\)]],
  "+ 8(r + 10)\[Lambda] + 160(r - 1) = 0"
}], "Section",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving for \[Lambda]", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
We will begin by solving for \[Lambda] as a function of r. We will do this \
symbolically and show the result in approximate form as well.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[r, \[Lambda], f, sol]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{\(f[r_]\), ":=", 
      StyleBox[\(3  \[Lambda]\^3 + 41\ \[Lambda]\^2 + 
          8 \((r + 10)\) \[Lambda] + 160\ \((r - 1)\)\),
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(sol[r_] = 
      Solve[f[r] \[Equal] 0, \[Lambda]] // 
        Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(N[%]\)}], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Evaluating the Solution for Different r Values", "Subsection"],

Cell["We can evaluate this solution for any value of r", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"sol", "[", 
        StyleBox["24",
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "//", 
      "N"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"sol", "[", 
        StyleBox["25",
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "//", "N"}]}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
Notice how small the real portion of the complex solutions are. Notice also \
that the real parts change signs between r = 24 and r = 25. Let's check it \
out for r = 24.737\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"sol", "[", 
        StyleBox["24.737",
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "//", "N"}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
The real portion of the solution is negligible here. If we knew the exact \
value to assign to r, the real part would become identically zero.\
\>", "Text"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Examining a Special Cubic", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can factor the cubic expression, ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`x\^3\)]],
  " + A",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\(\(\ \)\(x\^2\)\)\)]],
  "+ B x + AB, by hand, but we can do this with ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " as well."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(Clear[A, B, x]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(\(poly = x\^3 + A\ x\^2 + B\ x + A\ B;\)\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(Factor[poly]\)}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
From this we see the one real and two imaginary roots of the cubic.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(Solve[poly \[Equal] 0, x]\)], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Turning Our Cubic Into the Special Cubic", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "By taking our original cubic in \[Lambda], diving through by 3 (the \
coefficient of ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[Lambda]\^3\)]],
  "), then setting the product of the coefficients of ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[Lambda]\^2\)]],
  "and \[Lambda] equal to the constant term, we can determine the value of r \
required to arrive at the desired relationship."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"critr", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(41/3\ *8/3 \((r + 10)\) \[Equal] 160/3 \((r - 1)\)\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], ",", "r"}], "]"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
Evaluating our polynomial and solutions at this critical value of r, we get \
the following.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(f[r /. critr]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(Factor[f[r /. critr]]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(Solve[f[r /. critr] \[Equal] 0, \[Lambda]]\)}], "Input"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
